div.p:
Beſides euery regenerate man hath a a new heart, a renued ſpirit, which is a faithfull witneſſe, giuing teſtimony not to God, for that it needs not, nor to others, for that it cānot, but to the man who hath it, for that it muſt, of the truth of thoſe things, which it knows to be in him cōcerning Gods wil, & his own eternal welfare;
Pro. 14.5. ſeeing thē 
               a faithfull witneſſe will not lye, & the ſpirit of the penitēt teſtifieth the truth of his repentance may not he be as firmely perſuaded, as his heart faithfully witneſſeth the ſincerity of his conuerſion.
